  "description": "Per Tore Johannes Hallborg was a Swedish pastor who was born on August 20, 1905 in Växjö to the minister Aron H. and Sigrid Jacobsson. He married Brita Kärrfors in 1931 and had five children. Hallborg earned a Stud:ex from Växjö in 1923, a Bachelor of Theology from Lund University in 1925, a Master of Theology, practical theology exam and was ordained as a priest in the Växjö diocese in 1929. He served as a curate in Tjureda and Rydaholm, assistant pastor in Rydaholm and Båraryd, diocesan adjutant from 1931-35, acting vicar in Smedby from 1935-38, acting curate in Älmhult from 1939-40, and pastor there since 1941. He was a secretary of the diocesan council from 1931-35. He also published Kyrka o. Hem (Church and Home, a church monthly magazine in Växjö diocese) from 1934-35."
